xfit_city_1 <- seq(min(x_city_1),max(x_city_1),length=40)
yfit_city_1 <- dnorm(xfit_city_1,mean = mean(x_city_1),sd = sd(x_city_1))

Multiple regression (OLS)

City scale

Regressiondata_city<- city_log  %>%  dplyr::select(lnnight, lnf1,lnf2,lnf3,lnf4,lnf5)
city_multi_model <- lm( lnnight~ lnf2 +lnf3+ lnf4 +lnf5, data = Regressiondata_city)
tidy(city_multi_model)
## # A tibble: 5 x 5
##   term        estimate std.error statistic p.value
##   <chr>          <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1 (Intercept)   -2.44      4.10     -0.594  0.561 
## 2 lnf2           0.748     0.324     2.31   0.0349
## 3 lnf3           0.381     0.376     1.01   0.326 
## 4 lnf4          -0.290     0.350    -0.828  0.420 
## 5 lnf5          -0.208     0.442    -0.471  0.644
city_log <- city_log %>%
  mutate(model_final_res = residuals(city_multi_model))

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(city_multi_model)

qtm(city_log, fill = "model_final_res",title="Distribution of Residuals(City)")
## Variable(s) "model_final_res" contains positive and negative values, so midpoint is set to 0. Set midpoint = NA to show the full spectrum of the color palette.

coordsW_city <- city_log%>%
  st_centroid()%>%
  st_geometry()
## Warning in st_centroid.sf(.): st_centroid assumes attributes are constant over
## geometries of x
## Warning in st_centroid.sfc(st_geometry(x), of_largest_polygon =
## of_largest_polygon): st_centroid does not give correct centroids for longitude/
## latitude data
knn_coounty <-coordsW_city %>%
  knearneigh(., k=4)

city_knn <- knn_coounty %>%
  knn2nb()

knn_coounty_weight <- city_knn %>%
  nb2listw(., style="C")

city_Moran <- city_log %>%
  st_drop_geometry()%>%
  dplyr::select(model_final_res)%>%
  pull()%>%
  moran.test(., knn_coounty_weight)%>%
  tidy()

city_Moran
## # A tibble: 1 x 7
##   estimate1 estimate2 estimate3 statistic p.value method             alternative
##       <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl> <chr>              <chr>      
## 1     0.190     -0.05    0.0150      1.96  0.0249 Moran I test unde~ greater
